{"title_page": "Dee Hsu", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Chinese name|[[X\u00fa|Hsu]]}}{{infobox person\n| name = Dee Hsu\n| image = \u5c0fs\u4e52\u4e53\u6a02\u900f\u6642\u9593 01.png\n| alt = \n| caption = \n| native_name = \n| native_name_lang = zh\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1978|06|14}}\n| birth_place = [[Taipei]], Taiwan\n| occupation = Actress, singer, television host\n| years_active = 1994\u2013present\n| spouse = {{marriage|Mike Hsu|2005}}\n| children = {{unbulleted list|Elly Hsu (daughter)|Lily Hsu (daughter)|Alice Hsu (daughter)}}\n| family = Hsu Si-hsien (sister) <br> [[Barbie Hsu]] (sister)\n| awards = {{awards|award=[[Golden Bell Awards]]|name=40th [[Best Host in a Variety Programme(Golden Bell Awards)|Best Host in a Variety Programme]]<br />2005 ''[[Kangxi lai le]]'' with [[Kevin Tsai]]}}\n| module = {{Infobox Chinese|child=yes\n| p = X\u00fa X\u012bd\u00ec\n}}\n| module2 = {{infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| alias = \u5c0fS ({{zh|p=xi\u01ceo S}})\n | background = temporary\n| origin = Taiwan\n| genre = [[Mandopop]]\n| associated_acts = ASOS\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Dee Hsu''' ({{zh|t=\u5f90\u7199\u5a23|p=X\u00fa X\u012bd\u00ec|w=Hs\u00fc Hsi-ti}}; born 14 June 1978), more commonly known as Xi\u01ceo S or Little S (\u5c0fS), is a [[Taiwanese people|Taiwanese]] television host, actress, and singer, also formerly a [[ballroom dance]]r. Hsu is well known for her quick-witted caustic humor. From 2004 to 2015, she co-hosted ''[[Kangsi Coming]]'' with [[Kevin Tsai]]. The pair were awarded [[Best Host in a Variety Programme(Golden Bell Awards)|Best Host in a Variety Programme]] at the 40th [[Golden Bell Awards]] in 2005.<ref>{{in lang|zh}} [http://ent.sina.com.cn/v/2005-11-12/2139894593.html 40th Golden Bell Awards winners list \u2013 2005] 12 November 2005. Retrieved 9 June 2011</ref>\n\n== Life and career ==\nHsu was born in [[Taipei]], [[Taiwan]] on 14 June 1978, she was the youngest of the three sisters, with the eldest being Hsu Si-hsien, and the second elder sister being [[Barbie Hsu]].\n\nHsu sang in a duo with her sister Barbie Hsu, called \"S.O.S.\" (Sisters of Shu). Due to copyright issues with music labels, the group's name was changed to A.S.O.S. (All Sisters of Shu) in the late 90s.<ref>http://www.haibao.cn/star/1668/</ref>\n\nSince 1999, Hsu and her sister gradually put their singing career to rest. Hsu went on to host various TV programs, including [[Guess (variety show)|GUESS]] and [[Kangsi Coming]] (\u5eb7\u7199\u4f86\u4e86), which she joined in 2004, and has since been a top host/comedian in Taiwan. She also worked as a spokesperson for [[Shiatzy Chen]].\n\nIn 2004, Hsu collaborated with [[Show Lo]], her then co-host on [[100% Entertainment]], on a duet \"\u6200\u611b\u9054\u4eba\" (Love Expert) and co-starred with Luo in the music video. The track was released on Luo's second album ''[[Expert Show]]''.\n\nIn 2014, Hsu return to her singing career, and publish her first EP album \"Elephant DEE\" by using her new stage name Elephant DEE, which includes 5 songs. Dee Hsu wrote 4 songs including the lyrics and the rhythm, and 1 song called \u5fc3\u81df\u5674\u8840 is written by her sister [[Barbie Hsu]].\n\n== Personal life ==\nHsu married Taiwanese businessman Mike Hsu in 2005. They have three daughters, Elly, Lily and Alice.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u5c0fS\u7b54\u61c9\u7537\u53cb\u8a31\u96c5\u921e\u6c42\u5a5a \u7537\u53cb\u5bb6\u5883\u5bcc\u88d5 |url=http://tw.epochtimes.com/bt/5/5/30/n938127.htm |work=[[The Epoch Times]] |date=30 May 2005 |accessdate=6 December 2008 |language=zh |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081209053904/http://tw.epochtimes.com/bt/5/5/30/n938127.htm |archivedate=9 December 2008 }}</ref>\n\nIn August 2013, Hsu, her husband and her father-in-law (Xu Qing Xiang), were sued after being involved in the bread store chain \"Pang Da Ren\" scandal.<ref>{{cite web|last=\u4e2d\u56fd\u65b0\u95fb\u7f51|title=\u5c0fS\u56e0\u80d6\u8fbe\u4eba\u6848\u51fa\u5ead\u843d\u6cea \u82e5\u6d89\u8bc8\u6b3a\u6216\u88ab\u52245\u5e74(\u56fe)|url=http://www.chinanews.com/tw/2013/10-12/5368980.shtml|publisher=\u4e2d\u56fd\u65b0\u95fb\u7f51|accessdate=23 October 2013}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n=== Variety show ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role\n|-\n| 1998\u20132006 || ''[[Guess (variety show)|Guess Guess Guess]]'' \u6211\u731c\u6211\u731c\u6211\u731c\u731c\u731c|| Host\n|-\n| 1998\u20132006 || ''[[100% Entertainment]]'' \u5a31\u4e50\u767e\u5206\u767e || Host\n|-\n| 2004\u20132016 ||''[[Kangsi Coming]]'' \u5eb7\u7199\u6765\u4e86 || Host\n|-\n| 2007\u20132008 || ''Gourmet Secrets of the Stars'' || Host\n|-\n| 2016-now || ''S-style Show'' \u59d0\u59d0\u597d\u997f || Host\n|-\n| 2018-now || \u771f\u76f8\u5427\uff01\u82b1\u82b1\u4e16\u754c || Host\n|-\n| 2018\u20132019|| ''Sister's Flower Shop'' \u5c0f\u59d0\u59d0\u7684\u82b1\u5e97 || Host ||<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.iqiyi.com/a_19rrh3gfr1.html|title=\u300a\u5c0f\u59d0\u59d0\u7684\u82b1\u5e97\u300b|date=6 May 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2019 || \u6211\u4eec\u662f\u771f\u6b63\u7684\u670b\u53cb || Host\n|}\n\n=== Television series ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !!Role !!class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2002 || ''Six Friends'' ||Hua Tzu  ||\n|-\n| 2004 || ''[[Say Yes Enterprise]]'' ||Hsu Hsiao-hung ||\n|-\n| 2013 || ''PMAM'' ||Hsiao S || Cameo\n|-\n| 2018 || ''[[Meteor Garden (2018 TV series)|Meteor Garden]]'' ||Dao Ming Zhuang || Sister of Dao Ming Si\n|-\n|}\n\n===Film ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2008 || ''[[What on Earth Have I Done Wrong?!]]'' || || Cameo\n|-\n| 2017 || ''[[Didi's Dream]]'' || Shangguan Didi / Xu Chunmei ||\n|-\n|}\n\n===Voice dub===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" \n|-\n! Year !! Title!! Role\n|-\n|2004||''[[The Incredibles]]''||Mirage\n|-\n|2016||''[[Finding Dory]]''|| Dory\n|}\n\n=== Awards ceremony host ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Event !!class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2004 || 39th [[Golden Bell Awards]] ||\n|-\n| 2006 || [[17th Golden Melody Awards]] || Co-host (with [[Matilda Tao]])\n|-\n| 2008 || [[19th Golden Melody Awards]] || Co-host (with [[Matilda Tao]], [[Patty Hou]] and [[Barbie Hsu]])\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2010 ||[[21st Golden Melody Awards]] || Co-host (with [[Harlem Yu]])\n|-\n| [[47th Golden Horse Awards]] ||  Co-host (with [[Kevin Tsai]])\n|}\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n\n=== Golden Bell Awards ===\n{{awards table}}\n\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''Say Yes Enterprise''\n| [[Golden Bell Award for Best Supporting Actress|Best Supporting Actress]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2005\n| rowspan=4 |''[[Kangsi Coming]]''\n| rowspan=4 |[[Best Host in a Variety Programme(Golden Bell Awards)|Best Host in a Variety Programme]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| 2006\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2007\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2008\n| {{nom}}\n{{end}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb name|3872617}}\n* {{in lang|zh}} [http://t.sina.com.cn/dees Dee Hsu's Sina Microblog]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hsu, Dee}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1978 births]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Taipei]]\n[[Category:Taiwanese television personalities]]\n[[Category:21st-century Taiwanese actresses]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Chinese name|[[X\u00fa|Hsu]]}}{{infobox person\n| name = Dee Hsu\n| image = \u5c0fs\u4e52\u4e53\u6a02\u900f\u6642\u9593 01.png\n| alt = \n| caption = \n| native_name = \n| native_name_lang = zh\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1978|06|14}}\n| birth_place = [[Taipei]], Taiwan\n| occupation = Actress, singer, television host\n| years_active = 1994\u2013present\n| spouse = {{marriage|Mike Hsu|2005}}\n| children = {{unbulleted list|Elly Hsu (daughter)|Lily Hsu (daughter)|Alice Hsu (daughter)}}\n| family = Hsu Si-hsien (sister) <br> [[Barbie Hsu]] (sister)\n| awards = {{awards|award=[[Golden Bell Awards]]|name=40th [[Best Host in a Variety Programme(Golden Bell Awards)|Best Host in a Variety Programme]]<br />2005 ''[[Kangxi lai le]]'' with [[Kevin Tsai]]}}\n| module = {{Infobox Chinese|child=yes\n| p = X\u00fa X\u012bd\u00ec\n}}\n| module2 = {{infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| alias = \u5c0fS ({{zh|p=xi\u01ceo S}})\n | background = temporary\n| origin = Taiwan\n| genre = [[Mandopop]]\n| associated_acts = ASOS\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Dee Hsu''' ({{zh|t=\u5f90\u7199\u5a23|p=X\u00fa X\u012bd\u00ec|w=Hs\u00fc Hsi-ti}}; born 14 June 1978), more commonly known as Xi\u01ceo S or Little S (\u5c0fS), is a [[Taiwanese people|Taiwanese]] television host, actress, and singer, also formerly a [[ballroom dance]]r. Hsu is well known for her quick-witted caustic humor. From 2004 to 2015, she co-hosted ''[[Kangsi Coming]]'' with [[Kevin Tsai]]. The pair were awarded [[Best Host in a Variety Programme(Golden Bell Awards)|Best Host in a Variety Programme]] at the 40th [[Golden Bell Awards]] in 2005.<ref>{{in lang|zh}} [http://ent.sina.com.cn/v/2005-11-12/2139894593.html 40th Golden Bell Awards winners list \u2013 2005] 12 November 2005. Retrieved 9 June 2011</ref>\n\n== Life and career ==\nHsu was born in [[Taipei]], [[Taiwan]] on 14 June 1978, she was the youngest of the three sisters, with the eldest being Hsu Si-hsien, and the second elder sister being [[Barbie Hsu]].\n\nHsu sang in a duo with her sister Barbie Hsu, called \"S.O.S.\" (Sisters of Shu). Due to copyright issues with music labels, the group's name was changed to A.S.O.S. (All Sisters of Shu) in the late 90s.<ref>http://www.haibao.cn/star/1668/</ref>\n\nSince 1999, Hsu and her sister gradually put their singing career to rest. Hsu went on to host various TV programs, including [[Guess (variety show)|GUESS]] and [[Kangsi Coming]] (\u5eb7\u7199\u4f86\u4e86), which she joined in 2004, and has since been a top host/comedian in Taiwan. She also worked as a spokesperson for [[Shiatzy Chen]].\n\nIn 2004, Hsu collaborated with [[Show Lo]], her then co-host on [[100% Entertainment]], on a duet \"\u6200\u611b\u9054\u4eba\" (Love Expert) and co-starred with Luo in the music video. The track was released on Luo's second album ''[[Expert Show]]''.\n\nIn 2014, Hsu return to her singing career, and publish her first EP album \"Elephant DEE\" by using her new stage name Elephant DEE, which includes 5 songs. Dee Hsu wrote 4 songs including the lyrics and the rhythm, and 1 song called \u5fc3\u81df\u5674\u8840 is written by her sister [[Barbie Hsu]].\n\n== Personal life ==\nHsu married Taiwanese businessman Mike Hsu in 2005. They have three daughters, Elly, Lily and Alice.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u5c0fS\u7b54\u61c9\u7537\u53cb\u8a31\u96c5\u921e\u6c42\u5a5a \u7537\u53cb\u5bb6\u5883\u5bcc\u88d5 |url=http://tw.epochtimes.com/bt/5/5/30/n938127.htm |work=[[The Epoch Times]] |date=30 May 2005 |accessdate=6 December 2008 |language=zh |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081209053904/http://tw.epochtimes.com/bt/5/5/30/n938127.htm |archivedate=9 December 2008 }}</ref>\n\nIn August 2013, Hsu, her husband and her father-in-law (Xu Qing Xiang), were sued after being involved in the bread store chain \"Pang Da Ren\" scandal.<ref>{{cite web|last=\u4e2d\u56fd\u65b0\u95fb\u7f51|title=\u5c0fS\u56e0\u80d6\u8fbe\u4eba\u6848\u51fa\u5ead\u843d\u6cea \u82e5\u6d89\u8bc8\u6b3a\u6216\u88ab\u52245\u5e74(\u56fe)|url=http://www.chinanews.com/tw/2013/10-12/5368980.shtml|publisher=\u4e2d\u56fd\u65b0\u95fb\u7f51|accessdate=23 October 2013}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n=== Variety show ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role\n|-\n| 1998\u20132006 || ''[[Guess (variety show)|Guess Guess Guess]]'' \u6211\u731c\u6211\u731c\u6211\u731c\u731c\u731c|| Host\n|-\n| 1998\u20132006 || ''[[100% Entertainment]]'' \u5a31\u4e50\u767e\u5206\u767e || Host\n|-\n| 2004\u20132016 ||''[[Kangsi Coming]]'' \u5eb7\u7199\u6765\u4e86 || Host\n|-\n| 2007\u20132008 || ''Gourmet Secrets of the Stars'' || Host\n|-\n| 2016-now 