t]'' (October 2018)\n* \u201c[http://rolereboot.org/culture-and-politics/details/2018-10-halloween-2018-a-horror-film-for-the-timesup-era/ ''Halloween'' 2018: A Horror Film for the #TimesUp Era]\u201d\u2013''[http://rolereboot.org/ Role Reboot]'' (October 2018)\n* \u201c[http://rolereboot.org/culture-and-politics/details/2018-11-bohemian-rhapsodys-fumbling-representations-of-sexuality/ ''Bohemian Rhapsody''\u2018s Fumbling Representations of Sexuality]\u201d\u2013''[http://rolereboot.org/ Role Reboot]'' (November 2018)\n* \u201c[http://rougarou.org/2018/02/floating-the-yacht/ Floating the Yacht]\u201d\u2013Published in ''[http://rougarou.org/ Rougarou: Journal of Arts & Literature]'' (winter 2018)\n* \u201c[http://www.literaryorphans.org/playdb/dumbo-and-me-by-brett-riley/ ''Dumbo'' and Me]\u201d\u2013Published in ''[http://www.literaryorphans.org/playdb/ Literary Orphans]''\n* \u201c[http://www.rolereboot.org/culture-and-politics/details/2019-01-the-golden-globes-a-celebration-of-diversity-sort-of/ The Golden Globes: A Celebration of Diversity, Sort Of]\"\u2013Published in ''[http://rolereboot.org/ Role Reboot]'' (January 2019)\n* \u201c[http://rolereboot.org/culture-and-politics/details/2019-01-gillette-is-right-guys-we-can-get-better/ Gillette Is Right, Guys; We Can Get Better]\u201d\u2013Published in ''[http://rolereboot.org/ Role Reboot]'' (January 2019)\n* \u201c[http://rolereboot.org/culture-and-politics/details/2019-02-the-2019-grammys-a-soundtrack-for-change/ The 2019 Grammys: A Soundtrack for Change]\u201d\u2013Published in ''[http://rolereboot.org/ Role Reboot]'' (February 2019)\n* \u201c[http://rolereboot.org/culture-and-politics/details/2019-02-the-2019-oscars-an-improved-show-with-a-few-huge-missteps/ The 2019 Oscars: An Improved Show with a Few Huge Missteps]\u201d\u2013Published in ''[http://rolereboot.org/ Role Reboot]'' (February 2019)\n* \u201c[http://www.rolereboot.org/culture-and-politics/details/2019-03-meeting-a-familiar-enemy-jordan-peeles-us/ Meeting a Familiar Enemy: Jordan Peele\u2019s ''Us'']\u201d\u2013Published in ''[http://rolereboot.org/ Role Reboot]'' (March 2019)\n* \u201c''[http://rolereboot.org/culture-and-politics/details/2019-04-the-best-of-enemies-its-still-all-about-whiteness/ The Best of Enemies'': It\u2019s Still All about Whiteness]\u201d\u2013Published in ''[http://rolereboot.org/ Role Reboot]'' (April 2019)\n* \"[https://frictionlit.org/re-reading-avengers-1-10-from-a-contemporary-perspective/ Re-Reading Avengers #1-10 from a Contemporary Perspective]\"\u2014Published in ''[https://frictionlit.org/ F(r)iction''] (September 2019)\n* \"[https://www.underthegumtree.com/dreaming-in-stereo Dreaming in Stereo]\"\u2014Published in ''[https://www.underthegumtree.com/ under the gum tree]'' (October 2019)\n\n=== Short Fiction ===\n* \u201cGolgotha\u201d\u2014Published in ''[https://bigmuddyjournal.com/ Big Muddy, an Interdisciplinary Journal of the Mississippi River Valley]'' 9.1 (2009) pp. 59-66\n* \u201cLost and Found\u201d\u2014Published in ''[http://www.four-sep.com/pages/FirstClass.html First Class]'' 35.2 (2010) pp. 21-31\n* \u201cDoesn\u2019t Mean They\u2019re not Out to Get You\u201d\u2014Published in ''[http://thebroadkillreview.blogspot.com/ The Broadkill Review]'' 4.4 (July/August 2010)\n* \u201cThe Security System\u201d\u2014Published in ''[http://thebroadkillreview.blogspot.com/ The Broadkill Review]'' 4.5 (September/October 2010) pp. 38-40\n* \u201cThe Cat in the Backyard\u201d\u2014Published in ''[https://www.american.edu/cas/literature/folio/ Folio]'' (fall 2010/spring 2011 issue) pp. 96-102\n* \u201cAn Anecdote\u201d\u2014Published in ''[http://thebroadkillreview.blogspot.com/ The Broadkill Review]'' 5.1 (January/February 2011) pp. 11-13\n* \u201cDated\u201d\u2014Published in ''[http://thebroadkillreview.blogspot.com/ The Broadkill Review]'' 5.2 (March/April 2011) pp. 25-27\n* \u201cA Transcript Found on My Hard Drive (I)\u201d\u2014Published in ''[http://thebroadkillreview.blogspot.com/ The Broadkill Review]'' 5.3 (May/June 2011) pp. 63-64\n* \u201cJust Because You\u2019re Paranoid\u201d\u2014Published in ''[http://thebroadkillreview.blogspot.com/ The Broadkill Review]'' 5.4 (July/August 2011) pp. 62-65\n* \u201cOld Shoes\u201d\u2014Published in ''Metal Scratches'' issue 13 (2011) pp. 1-7\n* \u201cHook\u201d\u2014Published in ''[https://www.allegoryezine.com/ Allegory]'' 18.45 (spring/summer 2012)\n* \"[http://bluelakereview.weebly.com/a-face-to-die-for.html A Face to Die For]\"\u2014Published in ''[http://bluelakereview.weebly.com/ Blue Lake Review]'' (June 2012 update)\n* \u201cThe Hair on His Cape\u201d\u2014Published in ''[https://www.evansville.edu/majors/creativewriting/evansvilleReview.cfm The Evansville Review]'' Vol. XXII (2012) pp. 16-28\n*  \u201cHot Wheels for Jesus\u201d\u2014Published in ''[https://bigmuddyjournal.com/ Big Muddy, an Interdisciplinary Journal of the Mississippi River Valley],'' under the name Brendan West-Moreland, 12.1 (2012) pp. 184-193\n* \u201cPhone Tag\u201d\u2014Published in ''[http://www.mochilareview.com/ The Mochila Review]'' Vol. 14 (2012) pp. 80-88\n* \u201cAn Ending\u201d\u2014Published in ''Separate Worlds'' (January/February 2013) update, pp. 282-297\n* \u201cDoing It Like a Man\u201d\u2014Published in ''[https://uwosh.edu/wisconsinreview/ The Wisconsin Review]'' 46.2 (2013) pp. 27-34\n* \u201cFifth and Cedar\u201d\u2014Published in ''[http://sites.csn.edu/english/redrockreview/ Red Rock Review]'' 32 (fall 2013) pp. 37-43\n* \u201cAn Element of Blank\u201d\u2014Published in ''[https://www.evansville.edu/majors/creativewriting/evansvilleReview.cfm The Evansville Review]'' Vol. XXIII (2013) pp. 115-128\n* \u201c[https://solsticelitmag.org/content/what-lies-in-ambush/ What Lies in Ambush]\u201d\u2014Published in''[https://solsticelitmag.org/ Solstice Literary Magazine]'' (fall/winter 2015)\n* \u201c[https://burlesquepressllc.com/2015/08/11/orvilles-song-by-brett-riley/ Orville\u2019s Song]\u201d\u2014Published in ''[https://burlesquepressllc.com/the-burlesque-blog/ Burlesque Press Variety Show]'' (August 2015)\n* \u201cHyacinth\u201d\u2014Published in ''[http://thebroadkillreview.blogspot.com/ The Broadkill Review]'' 31 (October 2017 update)\n* \u201c[http://www.nthzine.com/tag/brett-riley/ An Element of Blank]\u201d\u2014Published in ''[http://www.nthzine.com/ Nth Degree]'' (February 2018)\n* \u201cSummer Home\u201d\u2014Published in ''[https://tetheredbyletters.com/friction-11/ f(r)iction]'' Vol. 11 (summer 2018) pp. 8-15\n* \u201c[https://www.thecourtshipofwinds.org/brett-riley Everyone Here Comes from Somewhere Else]\u201d\u2014Published in ''[https://www.thecourtshipofwinds.org/home-mainPage The Courtship of Winds]'' (winter 2018)\n* \u201c[http://baltimorereview.org/index.php/winter_2018/contributor/brett-riley Closed for Storm]\u201d\u2014Published in ''[https://baltimorereview.org/index.php The Baltimore Review]'' (winter 2018)\n* \u201cThy Rod and Thy Staff\u201d\u2014Published in ''[http://www.westtradereview.com/ West Trade Review]'' Vol. 10 (spring 2019) pp. 140-155\n* \u201c[https://solsticelitmag.org/content/salvation-is-a-joke-with-no-punchline/ Salvation is a Joke with No Punchline]\u201d\u2014Published in ''[https://solsticelitmag.org/ Solstice Literary Magazine]'' (spring 2019)\n* \u201c[http://ghosttownlitmag.com/brettriley Far Away from the Path and a Little Bit Lost]\u201d\u2014Published in ''[http://ghosttownlitmag.com/ Ghost Town]''\n* \u201c[http://bluestemmagazine.com/mating-behaviors-of-urban-white-males-in-the-southern-united-states/ Mating Behaviors of Urban White Males in the Southern United States]\u201d\u2014Published in ''[http://bluestemmagazine.com/ Bluestem]''\n* \"[http://www.barcelonareview.com/95/e_bar.html Alien]\"\u2014Published in [http://www.barcelonareview.com/index.html ''The Barcelona Review''] (October 2019)\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official website|https://officialbrettriley.com/about/}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century American writers]]\n[[Category:1970 births]]\n[[Category:Writers from Topeka, Kansas]]\n[[Category:Louisiana Tech University alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Arkansas at Monticello alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Louisiana at Monroe alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Louisiana at Monroe faculty]]\n[[Category:Louisiana State University faculty]]\n[[Category:University of Alabama faculty]]\n[[Category:College of Southern Nevada]]\n[[Category:American screenwriters]]\n[[Category:American male writers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American writer and college professor|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n'''Brett Alan Riley''' (born October 26, 1970) is an American writer and college professor. \n[[File:BrettRiley.jpg|thumb|Brett Riley]]\n\nRiley was born in [[Topeka, Kansas]], during his father\u2019s service in the [[United States Air Force]]. His family lived briefly in [[Austin, Texas]], before moving to [[Crossett, Arkansas]]. Except for a two-year period spent in [[Gloster, Mississippi]], and a one-year matriculation at [[Louisiana Tech University]], Riley lived in Crossett until the age of twenty-eight. He has since lived in [[Baton Rouge, Louisiana]]; [[Tuscaloosa, Alabama]]; and [[Las Vegas]], Nevada.\n\nIn 1994, Riley earned a BA in English from the [[University of Arkansas-Monticello]]. He completed his MA at the [[University of Louisiana-Monroe]] in 1997 and his PhD in Contemporary American Fiction and Film in 2006.\n\nSince 1995, Riley has worked in higher education. He taught at the University of Louisiana-Monroe (1995-1998), [[Louisiana State University]] (1998-2004, 2006), [[Baton Rouge Community College]] (2004-2006), and the [[University of Alabama]] (2006-2012). He currently teaches creative writing, American literature, and composition as a tenured professor at the [[College of Southern Nevada]].\n\nIn 2013, Ink Brush Press published Riley\u2019s collection of linked short stories, ''The Subtle Dance of Impulse and Light''.<ref>{{cite book |title=The Subtle Dance of Impulse and Light : a collection of episodes. |publisher=Ink Brush Press |isbn=9780988863200}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, his [[screenplay]], ''Candy\u2019s First Kiss'', won the New York Screenplay Contest\u2019s grand prize in horror/sci-fi; third place overall at the [[London Film Awards]] Screenwriting Competition; the Gold Prize in horror at the Beverly Hills Screenplay Contest; and Honorable Mention at the WeScreenplay International Screenwriting Competition. This script also won the Grand Prize in horror at the 2015 Hollywood Screenplay Contest. This screenplay was adapted from his [[short story]] entitled \u201cAn Element of Blank,\u201d first published in [[The Evansville Review]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Brett Riley \u2013 Nth Degree |url=http://www.nthzine.com/tag/brett-riley/}}</ref>\n\nRiley\u2019s debut novel, ''Comanche'', is forthcoming from Imbrifex Books in September 2020.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Riley |first1=Brett |title=Comanche |date=September 2020 |publisher=Imbrifex Books |isbn=9781945501364 |edition=First}}</ref>\n\nRiley lives in [[Henderson, Nevada]], with his wife and daughter. He has two other children, a son and a daughter, both of whom live in Arkansas. He has one granddaughter.\n\n== Publications ==\nBrett Riley has had dozens of short stories and essays published in various literary journals, magazines, and websites.\n\n=== Books ===\n* ''The Subtle Dance of Impulse and Light,'' Short Story Collection\u2014Published by [http://www.inkbrushpress.com/ Ink Brush Press] (April 2013)\n* ''Comanche: a novel''\u2014Published by [https://imbrifex.com/ Imbrifex Books] (forthcoming in September 2020)\n\n=== Screenplays ===\n* ''Candy's First Kiss''\n\n=== Creative Nonfiction ===\n* \u201c[http://rolereboot.org/culture-and-politics/details/2016-12-resistance-not-hate/ My Resistance is Not the Same as Your Hate]\u201d\u2013Published in ''[http://rolereboot.org/ Role Reboot]'' (December 2016)\n* \u201c[http://www.rolereboot.org/culture-and-politics/details/2017-07-white-privilege-matter-life-death/ When White Privilege is a Matter of Life and Death]\u201d\u2013Published in ''[http://rolereboot.org/ Role Reboot]'' (July 2017)\n* \u201c[http://www.rolereboot.org/life/details/2017-08-assault-bigotry-self-hatred-not-wounds-bleed/ Assault, Bigotry, and Self-Hatred: Not All Wounds Bleed]\u201d\u2013Published in ''[http://rolereboot.org/ Role Reboot]'' (August 2017)\n* \u201c[https://www.foliateoak.com/brett-riley.html Some Jokes Just Aren\u2019t Funny]\u201d\u2013Published in ''[https://www.foliateoak.com/ Foliate Oak Literary Magazine]''\n* \u201c[http://rolereboot.org/culture-and-politics/details/2017-10-las-vegas-dont/ We Are All Las Vegas, But We Don\u2019t Have to Be]\u201d\u2013Published in ''[http://rolereboot.org/ Role Reboot]'' (October 2017)\n* \u201c[http://www.wildviolet.net/2017/11/19/past-present-popcorn/#.XU36Y-hKiM9 Past, Present, Popcorn]\u201d\u2013Published in ''[http://www.wildviolet.net/ Wild Violet Literary Magazine]'' (November 2017)\n* \u201c[http://ghll.truman.edu/ghll29/Riley%20Was%20This%20Trip%20Really%20Necessary.html Was This Trip Really Necessary?]\u201d\u2013Published in ''[http://ghll.truman.edu/ Green Hills Literary Lantern]''\n* \u201c[http://www.rolereboot.org/culture-and-politics/details/2018-04-wont-watching-roseanne-reboot/ Why I Won\u2019t Be Watching the Roseanne Reboot]\u201d\u2013Published in ''[http://rolereboot.org/ Role Reboot]'' (April 2018)\n* \u201c[http://rolereboot.org/culture-and-politics/details/2018-06-the-true-horror-of-hereditary-patriarchy/ The True Horror of ''Hereditary'': Patriarchy]\u201d\u2013Published in ''[http://rolereboot.org/ Role Reboot]'' (June 2018)\n* \u201c[http://www.rolereboot.org/culture-and-politics/details/2018-08-why-you-need-to-see-the-mister-rogers-documentary/ Why You Need to See the Mister Rogers Documentary]\u201d\u2013Published in ''[http://rolereboot.org/ Role Reboot]'' (August 2018)\n* \u201c''[http://rolereboot.org/culture-and-politics/details/2018-08-blackkklansman-and-the-american-past-thats-still-present/ BlacKkKlansman'' and the American Past That\u2019s Still Present]\u201d\u2013Published in ''[http://rolereboot.org/ Role Reboot]'' (August 2018)\n* \u201c[http://rolereboot.org/culture-and-politics/details/2018-10-a-tale-of-two-women-on-joan-jett-and-dr-christine-blasey-ford/ A Tale of Two Women: On Joan Jett and Dr. Christine Blasey Ford]\u201d\u2013Published in ''[http://rolereboot.org/ Role Reboot]'' (October 2018)\n* \u201c[http://rolereboot.org/culture-and-politics/details/2018-10-halloween-2018-a-horror-film-for-the-timesup-era/ ''Halloween'' 2018: A Horror Film for the #TimesUp Era]\u201d\u2013''[http://rolereboot.org/ Role Reboot]'' (October 2018)\n* \u201c[http://rolereboot.org/culture-and-politics/details/2018-11-bohemian-rhapsodys-fumbling-representations-of-sexuality/ ''Bohemian Rhapsody''\u2018s Fumbling Representations of Sexuality]\u201d\u2013''[http://rolereboot.org/ Role Reboot]'' (November 2018)\n* \u201c[http://rougarou.org/2018/02/floating-the-yacht/ Floating the Yacht]\u201d\u2013Published in ''[http://rougarou.org/ Rougarou: Journal of Arts & Literature]'' (winter 2018)\n* \u201c[http://www.literaryorphans.org/playdb/dumbo-and-me-by-brett-riley/ ''Dumbo'' and Me]\u201d\u2013Published in ''[http://www.literaryorphans.org/playdb/ Literary Orphans]''\n* \u201c[http://www.rolereboot.org/culture-and-politics/details/2019-01-the-golden-globes-a-celebration-of-diversity-sort-of/ The Golden Globes: A Celebration of Diversity, Sort Of]\"\u2013Published in ''[http://rolereboot.org/ Role Reboot]'' (January 2019)\n* \u201c[http://rolereboot.org/culture-and-politics/details/2019-01-gillette-is-right-guys-we-can-get-better/ Gillette Is Right, Guys; We Can Get Better]\u201d\u2013Published in ''[http://rolereboot.org/ Role Reboot]'' (January 2019)\n* \u201c[http://rolereboot.org/culture-and-politics/details/2019-02-the-2019-grammys-a-soundtrack-for-change/ The 2019 Grammys: A Soundtrack for Change]\u201d\u2013Published in ''[http://rolereboot.org/ Role Reboot]'' (February 2019)\n* \u201c[http://rolereboot.org/culture-and-politics/details/2019-02-the-2019-oscars-an-improved-show-with-a-few-huge-missteps/ The 2019 Oscars: An Improved Show with a Few Huge Missteps]\u201d\u2013Published in ''[http://rolereboot.org/ Role Reboot]'' (February 2019)\n* \u201c[http://www.rolereboot.org/culture-and-politics/details/2019-03-meeting-a-familiar-enemy-jordan-peeles-us/ Meeting a Familiar Enemy: Jordan Peele\u2019s ''Us'']\u201d\u2013Published in ''[http://rolereboot.org/ Role Reboot]'' (March 2019)\n* \u201c''[http://rolereboot.org/culture-and-politics/details/2019-04-the-best-of-enemies-its-still-all-about-whiteness/ The Best of Enemies'': It\u2019s Still All about Whiteness]\u201d\u2013Published in ''[http://rolereboot.org/ Role Reboot]'' (April 2019)\n* \"[https://frictionlit.org/re-reading-avengers-1-10-from-a-contemporary-perspective/ Re-Reading Avengers #1-10 from a Contemporary Perspective]\"\u2014Published in ''[https://frictionlit.org/ F(r)iction''] (September 2019)\n* \"[https://www.underthegumtree.com/dreaming-in-stereo Dreaming in Stereo]\"\u2014Published in ''[https://www.underthegumtree.com/ under the gum tree]'' (October 2019)\n\n=== Short Fiction ===\n* \u201cGolgotha\u201d\u2014Published in ''[https://bigmuddyjournal.com/ Big Muddy, an Interdisciplinary Journal of the Mississippi River Valley]'' 9.1 (2009) pp. 59-66\n* \u201cLost and Found\u201d\u2014Published in ''[http://www.four-sep.com/pages/FirstClass.html First Class]'' 35.2 (2010) pp. 21-31\n* \u201cDoesn\u2019t Mean They\u2019re not Out to Get You\u201d\u2014Published in ''[http://thebroadkillreview.blogspot.com/ The Broadkill Review]'' 4.4 (July/August 2010)\n* \u201cThe Security System\u201d\u2014Published in ''[http://thebroadkillreview.blogspot.com/ The Broadkill Review]'' 4.5 (September/October 2010) pp. 38-40\n* \u201cThe Cat in the Backyard\u201d\u2014Published in ''[https://www.american.edu/cas/literature/folio/ Folio]'' (fall 2010/spring 2011 issue) pp. 96-102\n* \u201cAn Anecdote\u201d\u2014Published in ''[http://thebroadkillreview.blogspot.com/ The Broadkill Review]'' 5.1 (January/February 2011) pp. 11-13\n* \u201cDated\u201d\u2014Published in ''[http://thebroadkillreview.blogspot.com/ The Broadkill Review]'' 5.2 (March/April 2011) pp. 25-27\n* \u201cA Transcript Found on My Hard Drive (I)\u201d\u2014Published in ''[http://thebroadkillreview.blogspot.com/ The Broadkill Review]'' 5.3 (May/June 2011) pp. 63-64\n* \u201cJust Because You\u2019re Paranoid\u201d\u2014Published in ''[http://thebroadkillreview.blogspot.com/ The Broadkill Review]'' 5.4 (July/August 2011) pp. 62-65\n* \u201cOld Shoes\u201d\u2014Published in ''Metal Scratches'' issue 13 (2011) pp. 1-7\n* \u201cHook\u201d\u2014Published in ''[https://www.allegoryezine.com/ Allegory]'' 18.45 (spring/summer 2012)\n* \"[http://bluelakereview.weebly.com/a-face-to-die-for.html A Face to Die For]\"\u2014Published in ''[http://bluelakereview.weebly.com/ Blue Lake Review]'' (June 2012 update)\n* \u201cThe Hair on His Cape\u201d\u2014Published in ''[https://www.evansville.edu/majors/creativewriting/evansvilleReview.cfm The Evansville Review]'' Vol. XXII (2012) pp. 16-28\n*  \u201cHot Wheels for Jesus\u201d\u2014Published in ''[https://bigmuddyjournal.com/ Big Muddy, an Interdisciplinary Journal of the Mississippi River Valley],'' under the name Brendan West-Moreland, 12.1 (2012) pp. 184-193\n* \u201cPhone Tag\u201d\u2014Published in ''[http://www.mochilareview.com/ The Mochila Review]'' Vol. 14 (2012) pp. 80-88\n* \u201cAn Ending\u201d\u2014Published in ''Separate Worlds'' (January/February 2013) update, pp. 282-297\n* \u201cDoing It Like a Man\u201d\u2014Published in ''[https://uwosh.edu/wisconsinreview/ The Wisconsin Review]'' 46.2 (2013) pp. 27-34\n* \u201cFifth and Cedar\u201d\u2014Published in '